Newcastle disease in Israel
-------------------------
Extract from an e-mail received on 6 Mar 2001 from Dr Oded Nir, Director of
Veterinary and Animal Health Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural
Development, Beit Dagan:
One outbreak of Newcastle disease was reported in Beersheba district.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 4 Feb 2001.
Estimated date of first infection: 1 Feb 2001.
Total number of susceptible animals in the outbreak: 3500 layers
No. of cases: 350
No. of deaths: 70
Intracerebral pathogenicity index (ICPI) = 1.80
Control measures: stamping-out policy; quarantine and movement control
inside the country; testing; vaccination.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Israel had a small outbreak of NCD lasting for a couple of months in 1997.
Prior to that, it had been free of Newcastle Disease since 1982. - Mod.PC
